# vim: ts=40 noet nolist nohlsearch
#
#  Tips:
#    1|        to jump to description column
#    41|       to jump to hotkey column
#    81|       to jump to command column
#    ct<Tab>   to edit a field
#
#

# bspwm hotkeys
Close window	super + q	bspc node -c

Set window to floating	super + s	bspc node -t floating
Set window to tiled	super + d	bspc node -t tiled
Set window to fullscreen	super + f	bspc node -t fullscreen
Toggle monocle mode	super + t	bspc desktop -l next

Switch to last window	super + grave	bspc node -f last
Switch to last desktop	super + Tab	bspc desktop -f last

Switch current with last window	super + apostrophe	bspc node -s last
Switch current with biggest window	super + m	bspc node -s biggest

Move focus left	super + h	bspc node -f west
Move focus down	super + j	bspc node -f south
Move focus up	super + k	bspc node -f north
Move focus right	super + l	bspc node -f east

Move window left	super + shift + h	bspc node -s west
Move window down	super + shift + j	bspc node -s south
Move window up	super + shift + k	bspc node -s north
Move window right	super + shift + l	bspc node -s east

Switch to next window	super + c	bspc node -f next
Switch to previous window	super + shift + c	bspc node -f prev

Circulate nodes counter-clockwise	super + comma	bspc node @/ -C forward
Circulate nodes clockwise	super + period	bspc node @/ -C backward

Switch to previous desktop	super + bracketleft	bspc desktop -f prev
Switch to next desktop	super + bracketright	bspc desktop -f next

Put next window to the left	super + ctrl + h	bspc node -p west
Put next window below	super + ctrl + j	bspc node -p south
Put next window above	super + ctrl + k	bspc node -p north
Put next window to the right	super + ctrl + l	bspc node -p east
Cancel next window selection	super + ctrl + space	bspc node -p cancel

Expand window to the left	super + alt + h	bspc node -z left   -25   0
Expand window down	super + alt + j	bspc node -z bottom   0 +25
Expand window up	super + alt + k	bspc node -z top      0 -25
Expand window to the right	super + alt + l	bspc node -z right  +25   0

Retract window to the left	super + alt + shift + h	bspc node -z right  -25   0
Retract window down	super + alt + shift + j	bspc node -z top      0 +25
Retract window up	super + alt + shift + k	bspc node -z bottom   0 -25
Retract window to the right	super + alt + shift + l	bspc node -z left   +25   0

Select desktop on primary screen	super + {1-9}	bspc desktop -f 1-{1-9}
Select desktop on secondary screen	super + alt + {1-9}	bspc desktop -f 2-{1-9}
Select desktop on tetriary screen	super + ctrl + {1-9}	bspc desktop -f 3-{1-9}
Move to desktop on primary screen	super + shift + {1-9}	bspc node -d 1-{1-9}
Move to desktop on secondary screen	super + shift + alt + {1-9}	bspc node -d 2-{1-9}
Move to desktop on tetriary screen	super + shift + ctrl + {1-9}	bspc node -d 3-{1-9}

# wm independent hotkeys
Spawn terminal	super + Return	urxvtc
Run command	super + r	dmenu_launcher run
Restart sxhkd	super + Escape	restart sxhkd

Launch Neovim	super + n	urxvtc -e nvim
Launch IRC client	super + i	urxvtc -e irssi
Launch Chromium	super + b	chromium --disable-gpu-vsync

Lower volume	XF86AudioLowerVolume	volume down
Raise volume	XF86AudioRaiseVolume	volume up

Take screenshot (select area)	Print	screentool -s -u novaember
Take screenshot of desktop	ctrl + Print	screentool -S -u novaember
Take screenshot of window	alt + Print	screentool -W -u novaember

Move mouse to bottom of screen	Pause	xdotool mousemove_relative 0 9999
Reset wallpapers	ctrl + Pause	wp
Toggle compton on/off	super + Pause	toggle compton

Swap clipboard and primary selections	ctrl + Scroll_Lock	clipswap
Upload clipboard using nvpaste	alt + Scroll_Lock	nvpaste
Type contents of clipboard	ctrl + shift + Scroll_Lock	pastetype

Lock screen	alt + super + space	lock
